      </card>
      <card>
        <question><p>Compare a <code>for</code> loop's header with a <code>while</code> loop's header.</p></question>
        <answer><p>A <code>while</code> loop's header is just a condition; a <code>for</code> loop's header bundles initialization, condition, and update into one place.</p></answer>
