      <card>
        <question><p>Why does modifying size during an enhanced <code>for</code> loop fail rather than silently misbehave?</p></question>
        <answer><p>The iterator detects that the list was modified out from under it and throws <code>ConcurrentModificationException</code> to signal the problem.</p></answer>
