        <distractor><p><code>a.put(i, x)</code></p></distractor>
      </card>
      <card>
        <question><p>Is it safe to use <code>set</code> on an <code>ArrayList</code> while traversing it with an enhanced <code>for</code> loop?</p></question>
        <answer><p>Yes, because <code>set</code> does not change the size of the list.</p></answer>
        <distractor><p>No — any method call on the list during an enhanced <code>for</code> is unsafe.</p></distractor>
        <distractor><p>Only if the new value is the same object as the old one.</p></distractor>
